-- UniCredit CEO open to growth at Pioneer unit via partnerships, no sale
-- 
-- Wed Jul 09, 2014 09:40AM EDT
-- None



TURIN, ITALY July 9 (Reuters) - UniCredit <CRDI.MI> is ready to consider growth at its asset management unit Pioneer through partnerships but has excluded selling the subsidiary, the Italian lender's CEO said on Wednesday.

"There is nothing new on Pioneer. We are ready to consider accelerated growth via partnerships but will not sell it," Federico Ghizzoni said on the sidelines of a conference.